    "text": "A direct quantitative comparison requires thresholding the LSOG continuous probability map into a binary classification using a probability cutoff that matches the definition of LSOG presence in the Hagan et al. LiDAR map.",
    "topic": "Harmonize continuous vs discrete"
  },
  {
    "text": "The comparison should be restricted to spatial extents where both products overlap and the LSOG design-based estimates can be post-stratified to approximately match the model-based LiDAR domain.",
    "topic": "Reconcile inference frameworks"
  },
  {
    "text": "The term 'compared directly' must be disambiguated as either a qualitative visual comparison or a quantitative accuracy assessment, as the latter demands explicit harmonization steps.",
    "topic": "Define comparison type"
  },
  {
    "text": "The resolution mismatch can be resolved by resampling the LSOG 10m probabilities to the LiDAR mapping unit (e.g., modal aggregation) or by upsampling the LiDAR classification to 10m via nearest-neighbor, depending on the analysis goal.",
    "topic": "Match spatial resolutions"
  }
